<doc id="747419" wikidata="Q6096086" url="?curid=747419" title="Ivan Combe">
<text>Ivan DeBlois Combe (April 21, 1911 – January 11, 2000) was the American inventor of personal-care products, most notably Clearasil and Odor Eaters. In 1949 he established his eponymous company Combe Incorporated in White Plains, New York.

== Early life and career ==
Ivan DeBlois Combe was born in Fremont, Iowa, on April 21, 1911. Combe graduated from Northwestern University in 1933, and earned a law degree from the Northwestern University School of Law in 1936.

He became a salesman for Hydrox Ice Cream and the Wilbur Shoe Polish company before moving to New York City to work for the Young &amp; Rubicam advertising agency. He later joined Pharmacraft, a drug manufacturer, but in 1949, left his vice president position to create his own company.

== Death ==
Combe died in Greenwich, Connecticut on January 11, 2000.

== Legacy ==
After his death, Northwestern University named the Combe Tennis Center in his honor.

